        "cooked": "<p>At some point I ralize that most of the world worship the hi-dpi trend, but I still have and use native resolution of 1280x800 pixels and due to my eyes issues I must use only non-anti-aliased fonts with cleartype OFF. In this case the font in Signal for desktop looks extremely ugly.</p>\n<p>Please take a look on the images how ugly it is.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/5/3/53e79bfbff8b29e93f8cf7530a5c556aa0e1c706.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/53e79bfbff8b29e93f8cf7530a5c556aa0e1c706\" title=\"uglyfont2\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/5/3/53e79bfbff8b29e93f8cf7530a5c556aa0e1c706.jpeg\" alt=\"uglyfont2\" data-base62-sha1=\"bYfQK8VvhRLVgdhOBUKHBnZZPD0\" width=\"639\" height=\"500\" data-dominant-color=\"F7F7F8\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">uglyfont2</span><span class=\"informations\">655×512 34.8 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div><br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/4/24725844f3a792aa5b25b6f6cf73fcfccf27208e.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/24725844f3a792aa5b25b6f6cf73fcfccf27208e\" title=\"uglyfont1\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/4/24725844f3a792aa5b25b6f6cf73fcfccf27208e.jpeg\" alt=\"uglyfont1\" data-base62-sha1=\"5cqaDpWvTvjDLDcJfuzZFlh98PI\" width=\"432\" height=\"450\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">uglyfont1</span><span class=\"informations\">432×450 27.8 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>Could Signal simply inherit OS font family or allow to choose the font? I believe the current one is super cool font on hi-dpi screens with ClearType or whatever, but not for some.</p>\n<p>I use Win 11. I found that if I switch to Peresian language, beside the general language I don’t understand (my native is PL), the font also changes and looks quite good - so I am sure there is possible to have a font switch setting or so - because such functionality already exists.</p>\n<p>I suppose noone care of the nishe here, but it’s always worth to try (maybe change the “fa” font for “pl” usage as well pls?). Thanks!</p>",
